<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>for short • in short</xh5><p> <i>for short—</i>as an abbreviation: We call him Monty <u>for short</u>, his real name being Montgomery.</p><p> <i>in short</i>—(also: in short words) in brief; by way of summary: He became, <u>in short</u>, the finest actor on the American stage.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>in short order</b>—<i>very quickly; without delay:</i> <u>In short order</u> they tried, condemned and hanged all the prisoners.</p> </entry>
